sqft = len * (width + return) (in feet)
linear feet = height (ft)
flat feet = unit of one

pricing type is the unit of measurement (sq ft, linear feet, flat fee)

length = height

price is the base price

actual price = price per unit (pricing type is) * price * (1 * price plus)

price plus percentage - is the markup of the actual price 

Calico is a big vendor
Calico price is the same as price except for a specific customer with this specific shade

Missing a fabric field - multiple fabrics

three parts of fabric

Face fabric - main fab (calculate)
lining fabric - faces the window (calculate)

additional fabrics - make an appearance but no specific piece (not calcuated, documentation only)

Customer's own material - may be a flat fee, maybe zero, or a surcharge

fabric should be calculated similar fashion to product... pricing type, base price (no calico)

fabric should add up into the fabric subtotal

Lining Affects - pricing type * unit 
LInings have a property which is how wide it is, based on input width you need to calculate the total fabric for desired height

Stringing - A fixed cost is added on to the stringing based on selection
Std, 
Cord Lock, 
Clutch, 
Motor - different shades have different motors depending on somethign we don't know



